<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 7:43PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Hansford and
northwestern Ochiltree Counties through 815 PM CDT...
At 742 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Spearman, moving east at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Spearman, Waka and Farnsworth.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
